<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8389212>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. A–D. Burmeistera aeribacca (Grant 9153, type), leaf (A), leaf margin (B), flower (C) and berry (D). E–H. B. andakiana (Davidse et al. 5700, type), leaf (E), leaf margin (F), flower (G) and berry (H). I–L. B. asclepiadea (Rusby & Pennell 793, type), leaf (I), leaf margin (J), flower (K) and berry (L). White arrows in A, E and I point to ascending, secondary veins; white arrowheads in B, F and J point to third order veins; black arrows in F and J point to intramarginal veins; black arrowheads in B, F, and J point to hydathodes. Scale bars: 1 cm in A, E, I; 1 mm in B, F, J; 5 mm in C, D, G, H, K, L." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8389212/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

